President Trump and Governor Newsom held a press conference to discuss the wildfires in California, Oregon, and Washington. They expressed their condolences for those who lost their lives in the fires and praised the efforts of the firefighters and first responders. The President approved a major disaster declaration for California and has provided support to help combat the fires. They also discussed the need for better forest management and the impact of climate change on the severity of the fires. The Governor highlighted the importance of federal support, as 57% of the land in California is federal forest land. Various officials and representatives from different agencies also spoke about the ongoing efforts to fight the fires and protect affected communities.